  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NGO Funding - HHP, ERFS &amp; START</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The HPP enables partners to provide assistance that saves lives and maintains dignity whilst strengthening resilience and early recovery;
ERFS enables early action and response to reduce loss of life in sudden onset humanitarian emergencies or spikes in protracted crises;
The Start Fund enables early action and response to reduce loss of life in underfunded small to medium scale crises</narrative>
  </description>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Humanitarian Programme Plan (HPP) funding mechanism provides multi-annual funding to NGO partners for humanitarian programmes in predictable and protracted crises.
The Emergency Response Fund Scheme (ERFS) provides pre-positioned humanitarian financing to humanitarian NGOs at the beginning of each year for rapid responses to sudden onset crises
The Start Fund is a humanitarian pooled fund for underfunded small to medium scale crises</narrative>
  </description>
